    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>The SARS-CoV-2 variant Omicron is now under investigation. We evaluated cross-neutralizing activity against Omicron in COVID-19 convalescent patients (n=23) who had received two doses of an mRNA vaccination (BNT162b2 or mRNA-1273). Surprisingly and interestingly, after the second vaccination, the subjects\u2019 neutralizing antibody titers including that against Omicron all became seropositive, and significant fold-increases (21.1\u201352.0) were seen regardless of the subjects\u2019 disease severity. Our findings thus demonstrate that at least two doses of mRNA vaccination to SARS-CoV-2 convalescent patients can induce cross-neutralizing activity against Omicron.</jats:p>",
